A social media post highlighting ByteDance's new open-source document parsing framework called Dolphin. The framework is notable for being fully open-source, which allows developers and researchers to freely use, modify, and contribute to the tool.

This French-language blog post from Kompozite focuses on explaining the CO2 equivalent (CO2e) as a crucial unit of measurement for greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions. The article aims to help readers understand why this standardized metric is important for comparing and quantifying different types of greenhouse gases. CO2 equivalent allows for a comprehensive assessment of global warming potential by converting various greenhouse gases into a common scale based on their impact on climate change. By using this standardized measurement, scientists, policymakers, and organizations can more effectively track, compare, and communicate the environmental impact of different gases over different time horizons, which is essential for developing climate change mitigation strategies.
